// §3.5 Rule 4 — a local binding `red` shadows the variant in a rule-4
// (struct field with named enum type) position. The binding wins (i64
// vs RGB) → type error when the field expects RGB.
RGB is enum red, green, blue
red is 99
Palette is struct { accent is green as RGB }
// Rule-4 context (struct field with named enum type) — binding `red`
// wins over variant RGB.red, producing a type error.
bad is { accent is red } as Palette
